06/07/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Serbia-Montenegro President Svetozar Marovic makes his first official visit to Macedonia on Tuesday (6 July).
He is scheduled to meet with Macedonian President Branko Crvenkovski, Parliament Speaker Ljupco Jordanovski and Prime Minister Hari Kostov.
An agreement on legal assistance will be signed, as well as an accord on protecting the rights of the Macedonian minority in Serbia-Montenegro and the Serb minority in Macedonia.
Also Tuesday, Skopje will host a roundtable meeting on media independence and freedom of speech.
The forum is being organised by the Macedonian Institute for Media.
(MIA, Makfax - 06/07/04)
